Unfortunately, I don't think it's possible, but I really like the idea. One option is that you can use {% dnd_module %} tags to specify and add specific modules to your drag and drop areas. This way, only the specified modules will be added to the template by default. But, keep in mind that the content editor will still be able to add other modules to the dnd_area if they choose to do so.

For example:
```{% dnd_area "unique_name", class="main" %}
  {% dnd_module path="custom/module/path" %}
  {% end_dnd_module %}
{% end_dnd_area %}```
Another option could be to setup custom sections and then use those sections inside of the area tags but again this would just act as a template and would necessarily restrict
